Response:
"Our(1+1)D simulations are proof-of-concept for the reconstruction algorithm. The framework generalizes to higher dimensions. Specifically:

· For (2+1)D boundary (3D CFT), we reconstruct (3+1)D bulk
· The key equations scale with dimension: $g_{\mu\nu} = \mathcal{N}[\det C]^{-1/d}C_{\mu\nu}$
· Our numerical methods extend naturally to tensor networks in higher dimensions"

Anticipated Question 2: "What about diffeomorphism invariance?"

Response:
"Diffeomorphism invariance emerges as agauge symmetry of the correlation tensor $C_{\mu\nu}$. Under $\Psi \to e^{i\Lambda}\Psi$, we have:
\delta C_{\mu\nu} = \partial_\mu\partial_\nu\Lambda


but$\delta(\det C^{-1/4}C_{\mu\nu}) = 0$ for appropriate boundary conditions, exactly reproducing diffeomorphism invariance."

